  "name": "debugtools-map-hub-modern-debug",
  "description": "Map-phase debug hub entry (Issue #11 slice 2). Reuses the proven Chapter 2 story-mode frame prefix from debugtools-hub-modern-debug.json through frame 14164 (the last of that scenario's own periodic dialogue-clearing A-presses; frame prefixes beyond 14164 in the original fixture press A again at 14170 on an empty map tile, which opens the vanilla System Menu and permanently breaks PlayerPhase_MainIdle's idle loop -- this scenario truncates strictly before that point so the map stays genuinely interactive throughout). FE8_EXPANSION_DEBUGTOOLS_MAP_HOTKEY_MASK (SELECT+L) is pulsed twice (14200-14206, then 14260-14266) while PlayerPhase_MainIdle is genuinely idle: hubOpenCount goes from its pre-existing baseline of 1 (this run's earlier title-hub launch of Chapter 2) to 2 after the first pulse and stays at 2 after the second, proving DebugTools_OpenHub's reentrancy guard (sHubActive) rejects the repeat exactly as it does at the title screen -- and proving the map hotkey is a distinct combo from the title/prep hotkeys and from bare R/L/START (ordinary map controls are never double-fired). DOWN then A selects the Weather action: the hub closes (sHubActive 1->0) and the real dormant DebugMenu_WeatherDraw/Idle/Effect (src/bmdebug.c, unmodified) are driven for the first time ever in this codebase's runtime history through a bounded one-item orphan submenu (src/debugtools_actions.c). Two RIGHT presses are delivered into DebugMenu_WeatherIdle exactly as a player would. B then returns to the hub (hubOpenCount 2->3, sHubActive 0->1, cursor reset to slot 0 -- hence the extra DOWN to reach Fog instead of one). A on Fog opens its own bounded submenu (hubOpenCount stays 3, sHubActive 1->0) and delivers one RIGHT into the real dormant DebugMenu_FogIdle. B returns to the hub again (hubOpenCount 3->4, sHubActive 0->1), and a final B closes the hub for good (sHubActive 1->0, hubOpenCount stays 4 -- the hub's own Back/cancel path never reopens anything, unlike each submenu's onEnd). gPlaySt.chapterWeatherId and gPlaySt.chapterVisionRange are probed at every checkpoint and are proven to stay exactly 0x00 across the whole run: this is expected, not a defect. DebugMenu_WeatherIdle only ever mutates state through Proc_Find(ProcScr_DebugMonitor)->unk_58, and ProcScr_DebugMonitor's own script table (src/bmdebug.c, unmodified) is a single PROC_END -- which Proc_Start resolves synchronously (ProcCmd_DELETE -> Proc_End) before Proc_Start even returns, so Proc_Find(ProcScr_DebugMonitor) can never observe a live instance no matter which caller starts it (src/sio_menu.c's own original dormant call site has the exact same property) -- a pre-existing, untouchable dormant-code characteristic, not something this slice introduces or may fix. Separately, DebugMenu_FogIdle recomputes vision range from GetROMChapterStruct(gPlaySt.chapterIndex)->initialFogLevel on this non-skirmish story map, and Chapter 2's initialFogLevel data value is 0 -- so toggling legitimately settles back to 0 on this particular chapter, by chapter data, not by code defect. Both are confirmed safe, non-persistent, side-effect-free invocations of the real dormant handlers: no crash, no corruption, no drift from the expected value, consistent with the WHY section's framing of Weather/Fog as dormant and non-persistent. gBmSt.playerCursor.x/.y are probed throughout to prove the player map is never left in a non-interactive state: unchanged at (0x06, 0x03) through the entire hub/submenu sequence, then a final RIGHT after the hub is fully closed moves it to (0x07, 0x03), proving ordinary map control is fully restored.",
